### Set 5: REST API Testing File
### Use with "REST Client" extension in VS Code

@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

# ==========================================
# Q1: Student Login (MongoDB + Middleware)
# ==========================================

### Register
POST http://localhost:6001/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "student1",
    "password": "password123"
}

### Login
POST http://localhost:6001/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "student1",
    "password": "password123"
}

### View Profile (Paste token from login above)
GET http://localhost:6001/profile
Authorization: {{token}}


# ==========================================
# Q2: File Compression (Upload/Download)
# ==========================================

### Upload text for compression
POST http://localhost:6002/compress
Content-Type: text/plain

This is a long piece of text that I want to compress using the zlib module in Node.js.


# ==========================================
# Q3: Employee Portal (RBAC)
# ==========================================

### Admin View (All data)
GET http://localhost:6003/employees?role=admin

### User View (Own profile only)
GET http://localhost:6003/employees?role=user&id=102


# ==========================================
# Q4: Notes API (CRUD + Ownership)
# ==========================================

### Create Note
POST http://localhost:6004/notes
Content-Type: application/json
userid: user123

{
    "title": "My Secret Note",
    "content": "This belongs to user123 only."
}

### Get My Notes
GET http://localhost:6004/notes
userid: user123


# ==========================================
# Q5: Feedback + LLM
# ==========================================

### Submit Feedback
POST http://localhost:6005/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "text": "I really enjoyed the training session, it was very helpful and informative."
}


